criteria.driver_alignment:
Discover: defined objective to create a reusable script for financial questions; 
Implement: coded and explained cost of equity and WACC components in the script; 
Validate: independently recalculated and confirmed the WACC result; 
Reflect: interpreted how leverage and sensitivity (beta, MRP) affect WACC.

Discover: set objective to build a reusable script for financial calculations; 
Implement: coded the CAPM cost-of-equity formula into the script; 
Validate: ran sensitivity checks showing how beta changes cost of equity and confirmed outputs; 
Reflect: interpreted implications (e.g., higher beta → higher cost of equity, firm comparisons).

Discover: set clear objective to build a reusable financial script; 
Implement: coded WACC including the after-tax treatment of debt (1 − corporate tax rate); 
Validate/Reflect: validated WACC numerically and reflected that additional debt lowered WACC (tax-shield effect).

Discover: set objective to build a reusable financial script; 
Implement: coded WACC with the after-tax debt term (1 − corporate tax rate); 
Validate/Reflect: validated WACC numerically and observed that increasing debt reduced WACC, indicating the tax-shield effect.

Discover: set objective to produce a reusable script for financial analysis; 
Implement: computed WACC and produced numeric outputs used for decision-making; 
Validate: confirmed WACC numerically (11.22%); 
Reflect: adjusted WACC as a project-specific hurdle (US vs international) and recommended financing strategy based on its impact.

